    "failure_scenario": "A new always-present production endpoint widens attack surface and depends solely on an env-var check to stay inert; a future refactor that sets COVERAGE in a prod-adjacent env, or a regression in enabled(), exposes process internals and a CPU-heavy coverage dump to anonymous POSTs. It also permanently couples the production route namespace to test tooling."
  },
  {
    "file": "scripts/coverage/enrich-lcov.ts",
    "line": 2459,
    "summary": "enrich-lcov.ts fabricates DA:N,1 hit records for every non-blank/non-comment source line that V8 didn't probe, in any file that has at least one covered line — turning partially-executed files into near-100% before upload to Codecov. The deeper fix is to report only what V8 actually measured (statement/branch granularity) rather than synthesizing hits.",
    "failure_scenario": "Codecov numbers and the planned 80% patch gate become systematically inflated and untrustworthy: a file where one function ran but most branches didn't will report near-full line coverage, so the gate (once flipped to required) passes PRs that are largely untested, defeating the purpose of the pipeline."
  },
  {
    "file": ".github/workflows/coverage.yml",
    "line": 343,
    "summary": "Server coverage flush depends on a fragile chain of OS-level mechanics — setsid process groups, /tmp/next.pid, pgid lookups, pkill -USR2 -f 'next-server', SIGUSR2-then-SIGINT ordering, and PID-suffixed coverage/server-cdp-<pid>.json globbing — to capture Next's in-process Inspector dump. The deeper fix is an app-level flush endpoint/IPC that doesn't reverse-engineer Next's worker process tree.",
    "failure_scenario": "Any Next.js upgrade that renames the 'next-server' process, changes worker forking, or alters signal handling silently breaks the SIGUSR2 dump; server.lcov comes back empty or partial and is reported as a coverage drop rather than a tooling break, and there is no assertion that the dump was non-empty before upload."
  },
  {
    "file": "supabase/functions/_coverage/serve.ts",
    "line": 4700,
