    "failure_scenario": "The moment any function flips verify_jwt=true (a security hardening), the coverage harness serves it unauthenticated and the suite passes, hiding that auth is bypassed in the test topology; separately, a Deno upgrade changing the Deno.serve signature or namespace descriptor breaks handler capture for all functions and reports 0% edge coverage as a test regression."
  },
  {
    "file": "supabase/functions/_shared/GitHubWrapper.ts",
    "line": 388,
    "summary": "requireOctoKit + AppNotInstalledError are exported but requireOctoKit is never called anywhere (dead on arrival); the async worker relies on AppNotInstalledError being thrown from ensureClassGithubTeams instead. The deeper fix is to drop the unused export or actually route callers through it.",
    "failure_scenario": "Dead public API in a shared module invites future callers to adopt an unexercised path (zero coverage, by this PR's own admission) and creates maintenance ambiguity about which octokit accessor is canonical; it also signals the GitHub-init feature was only partially wired before being bundled into the coverage PR."
  },
  {
    "file": "next.config.ts",
    "line": 86,
    "summary": "Production runtime behavior is forked on COVERAGE=1 inside next.config.ts (staleTimes dynamic/static set to 0, productionBrowserSourceMaps on, SWC minify off, server source-map devtool) so the build measured for coverage is not the build that ships. The deeper fix is to accept that coverage measures a different artifact and document/limit the divergence, rather than threading prod config through a test flag.",
    "failure_scenario": "Coverage (and the Playwright run feeding it) exercises an un-minified, cache-disabled build, so client/server coverage and any behavior it 'verifies' don't reflect the minified, staleTimes:30 production bundle; minifier-only or RSC-cache-only bugs are invisible to the pipeline, and the config branch is a standing footgun if COVERAGE ever leaks into a real build env."
  }
]
```

